  "title": "Simple circuits - why are bulbs 1 and 2 lit or not",
  "content": {
    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a rectangular circuit diagram that has a battery, an open switch, a closed switch, and two lightbulbs. The circuit has three horizontal branches and two vertical branches. The top horizontal branch has the battery. The middle horizontal branch has a lightbulb labeled Bulb 1. The bottom horizontal branch has a lightbulb labeled Bulb 2. From top to bottom, the right vertical branch has the open switch labeled Switch 1 between the top and middle horizontal branches, and has the closed switch labeled Switch 2 between the middle and bottom horizontal branches.\" src=\"/images/38f93b7feedf59743f191a17d7fe1020.svg\"></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">The figure shows a circuit that includes a battery, two lightbulbs, and two switches. Switch <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> is open and Switch <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> is closed. Are the two bulbs lit or unlit, and what evidence or reasoning supports the claim?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i4",
    "choices": [
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The bulbs are lit. Bulbs <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> are in a closed loop with each other and are connected to the battery terminal on the left.</p>",
        "value": "i1"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The bulbs are lit. Electrons can move from the left terminal of the battery, rightward through Bulb <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span>, and then leftward through Bulb <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span> before returning to the battery.</p>",
        "value": "i2"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The bulbs are unlit. The wrong side of the battery is connected to the closed loop containing bulbs <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1\"><math alttext=\"1\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>1</mn></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2\"><math alttext=\"2\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn></math></span></span>.</p>",
        "value": "i3"
      },
      {
        "label": "<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The bulbs are unlit. The battery is not connected in a closed loop with either of the bulbs.</p>",
        "value": "i4"
      }
    ]
  },
